{"lemma":"بَغْلَة","slug":"بَغْلَة","root":"ب.غ.ل","root_slug":"ب-غ-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-غ-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2944","n2947"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%BA%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the offspring of a jack and a mare, a mule","examples":[{"text":"وَخَلَقَ […] الْخَيْلَ وَالْبِغَالَ وَالْحَمِيرَ لِتَرْكَبُوهَا وَزِينَةً","english":"And [God] created horses, mules, and asses for you to ride on and as an embellishment."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"In view of the Sabaean Old South Arabian 𐩨𐩶𐩡 (bġl), attested once from the 1ˢᵗ century CE, Arabic has more likely borrowed thence and not from Ge'ez በቅል (bäḳl) as formerly claimed, but the Old South Arabian may be an Old Arabic loanword as well, mule breeding only introduced not long before from the North, thus an unknown-origin borrowing."},"ipa":["/baɣl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2944","headword_ar":"بَغُلَ","root":"bgl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buguwlapN","text_ar":"بُغُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabal~ada","text_ar":"تَبَلَّدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He affected stupidity, dulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want of intelligence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became submissive, and humble;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) [See also 2.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagalahumo","text_ar":"بَغَلَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2947","headword_ar":"بَغْلٌ","root":"bgl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mule;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animal generated between the he-ass and the mare"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the horse and the she-ass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bag~aAlN","text_ar":"بَغَّالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so in a verse of Jereer: (S, Sgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abogalN","text_ar":"اَبْغَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] (JK) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abogaAlN","text_ar":"اَبْغَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [also] a pl. of pauc., (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigaAlN","text_ar":"بِغَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Msb, K,) a pl. of mult.; (Msb;) and quasi-pl. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maboguwlaA='u","text_ar":"مَبْغُولَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of mules"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigaAl","text_ar":"بِغَال"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * S:) the female is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagolapN","text_ar":"بَغْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagalaAtN","text_ar":"بَغَلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigaAlN","text_ar":"بِغَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) See 2, in two places. You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN fiyhi A^abowaAlu AlbigaAli","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ فِيهِ اَبْوَالُ البِغَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road in which is the urine of mules"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a difficult road."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnapu A^aEoqaru mino bagolapK","text_ar":"فُلَانَةُ اَعْقَرُ مِنْ بَغْلَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a woman is more barren than a she-mule"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albagolu nagolN wa huwa lahu A^aholN","text_ar":"البَغْلُ نَغْلٌ وَ هُوَ لَهُ اَهْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mule is a bastard, and he is a relation to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is a bastard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And as the mule suggests the idea of evil disposition, or perverseness, and roughness, you say, in describing him who is low, or ignoble,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa bagolN nagolN","text_ar":"هُوَ بَغْلٌ نَغْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is a mule, a bastard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib, TA.) The people of Egypt say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otaraY fulaAnN bagolapF HasonaA='a","text_ar":"اِشْتَرَى فُلَانٌ بَغْلَةً حَسْنَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one bought a beautiful"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoti baniY fulaAnK bigaAlN","text_ar":"بَيْتِ بَنِى فُلَانٍ بِغَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the house of the sons of such a one are slaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female slaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otarayotu mino bigaAli Alyamano wa l`kino bigaAliY Alv~amano","text_ar":"اِشْتَرَيْتُ مِنْ بِغَالِ اليَمَنْ وَ لٰكِنْ بِغَالِى الثَّمَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I bought of the slaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female slaves, of El-Yemen, but for a high price"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Sgh","JK","Msb","K"]}]}}